selfEmployed.title: Find free debt advice
selfEmployed.heading: Advice providers for small business owners or self-employed
selfEmployed.content: Here's where you can get free debt advice if you're a small business owner or self-employed.

sections.heading: Business Debtline (England and Wales)
sections.content: Business Debtline is a charity run by the Money Advice Trust. We are a free debt advice service for the self-employed and small businesses in England, Wales and Scotland. We have helped thousands of people deal with their debts. Our team of expert debt advisers care about improving your situation and will help you to take control of your debts.
sections.address: Tricorn House, 51 - 53 Hagley Road, Edgbaston, Birmingham, B16 8TP
sections.linkText: Business Debtline (England and Wales) (opens in a new tab)

online.heading: Where to get free debt advice online
online.content: Here's where you can get free debt advice online. This usually includes self-help tools and the option to speak to an adviser using live chat.You can also go back to view debt advice options by phone or in person.

sections.heading: Debt Advice Foundation
sections.content: Debt Advice Foundation is a national debt advice and education charity offering free, confidential support and advice to anyone worried about debt.
sections.linkText: Debt Advice Foundation (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: PayPlan
sections.content: PayPlan’s online debt solution tool, PlanFinder, can give you a personalised debt solution in as little as 15 minutes. They also offer free live chat and email support for immediate help.
sections.linkText: PayPlan (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: Money Wellness
sections.content: At Money Wellness, we offer confidential debt advice and ongoing support. There are lots of ways we help our customers, from budgeting tips to negotiating lower monthly payments with lenders to getting unaffordable debt written off. With 30 years of experience, we can help you live more and stress less.
sections.linkText: Money Wellness (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: National Debtline
sections.content: National Debtline offers free debt advice online through its digital advice tool and its web guides, fact sheets and sample letters.
sections.linkText: National Debtline (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: StepChange Debt Charity
sections.content: Debt happens. Let’s deal with it. In our 30 years, StepChange have helped over five million people through challenging times. Use our free and flexible online advice service with expert debt advisors on-hand to help you explore your options to pay, manage or write off debt.
sections.linkText: StepChange Debt Charity (opens in a new tab)

telephone.heading: Where to get free debt advice by telephone
telephone.content: Here's where you can get free debt advice over the phone. Advisers are often available Monday to Saturday, including evenings.You can also go back to view debt advice options online or in person.

sections.heading: Debt Advice Foundation
sections.content: Debt Advice Foundation is a national debt advice and education charity offering free, confidential support and advice to anyone worried about debt.

sections.heading: PayPlan
sections.content: PayPlan’s supportive, non-judgemental team of advisers help thousands of people beat their debts every year, and treat all of their calls with the strictest confidence.

sections.content: No advice provided for Wales

sections.content: At Money Wellness, we offer confidential debt advice and ongoing support. There are lots of ways we help our customers, from budgeting tips to negotiating lower monthly payments with lenders to getting unaffordable debt written off. With 30 years of experience, we can help you live more and stress less.
sections.linkText: Money Wellness (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: National Debtline
sections.content: National Debtline has helped millions of people with their debts. They’ll talk you through options and give clear advice on how to take back control.

sections.heading: StepChange Debt Charity
sections.content: Call the UK’s leading debt charity. We help change the lives of thousands of people every week. Get free, confidential advice and practical solutions to help you deal with your debts.

sections.heading: Citizens Advice
sections.content: If you’re having issues with money or debt, you can: talk to us online about a debt problem using chat - we can usually help between 9am and 8pm Monday to Friday and between 9.30am and 1pm Saturday call our debt helpline - it's available 9am to 8pm Monday to Friday and 9.30am to 1pm Saturday Debt helpline: 0800 240 4420 Relay UK - if you can't hear or speak on the phone, you can type what you want to say: 18001 then 0800 240 4420 You can use Relay UK with an app or a textphone. There's no extra charge to use it. Find out how to use Relay UK on the Relay UK website. The debt helpline is not available on public holidays. Calls are free from mobiles and landlines.

faceToFace.heading: Where to get local debt advice
faceToFace.content: Here's where you can get free help from local debt advisers face-to-face. We list the eight closest to the location you entered, with the nearest first.You can also go back to view debt advice options online or by phone.

sections.heading: CAP Oxford St. Ebbe's Debt Centre
sections.content: We are a charity that provides free face to face debt advice in your own home, with ongoing support available by telephone. Give our friendly team a call on 0800 328 0006 or visit capuk.org to find out more.
sections.linkText: CAP Oxford St. Ebbe's Debt Centre (opens in a new tab)

sections.heading: Oxford Citizens Advice Bureau
sections.linkText: Oxford Citizens Advice Bureau (opens in a new tab)
